The paper deals with the complexity of first-order model checking on partially ordered sets (posets), which is a topic related to logic and discrete mathematics (cs.LO and cs.DM). The concept of width of a poset is also relevant to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper presents an algorithm for FO model checking on posets, which involves computational complexity and complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the application of FO model checking to posets has potential implications for artificial intelligence and knowledge representation (cs.AI).
